details: The word Algorithm means ” A set of finite rules or instructions to be followed in calculations or other problem-solving operations ” Or ” A procedure for solving a mathematical”.
A data structure is a storage that is used to store and organize data. It is a way of arranging data on a computer so that it can be accessed and updated efficiently. data structure
Discrete mathematics is the branch of mathematics dealing with objects that can consider only distinct, separated values. Mathematical inductions & set is the part of discrete.
The compiler is software that converts a program written in a high-level language (Source Language) to a low-level language (Object/Target/Machine Language/0’s, 1’s).

In some ways, artificial intelligence is the opposite of natural intelligence. If living creatures can be said to be born with natural intelligence, man-made machines can be said to possess artificial intelligence.

Machine Learning is the field of study that gives computers the capability to learn without being explicitly programmed. ML is one of the most exciting technologies that one would have ever come across.
Cryptography is technique of securing information and communications through use of codes so that only those person for whom the information is intended can understand it and process it.
